Minister of Science and Technology, Dr. Ogbonnaya Onu said the problems bedeviling the power sector have been identified and are being resolved. He said the problem stems from the non deployment of science and technology to efficiently utilise the countries enormous energy resources. Onu, who spoke yesterday in Abuja, at the opening of the National Energy summit, urged Nigerians not to lose hope because the energy future of the country is bright. He added that President Muhammadu Buhari has been working very hard to provide the enabling environment for private investment in the energy sector.